3-Day Adventure Guide

Meet Neon!

Everything you need to know for the best weekend ever with your new Schnoodle best friend.

The Main Character

Ready for some bounciness?

Neon's Stats

Formerly known as Ferren

Breed

Schnoodle

Age

7 Months

Weight

8.5 lbs

Birthday

July 4, 2025

Vibe Check

Neon is super intelligent and high energy. He's vocal, curious, and thrives on mental stimulation. He's in his "teenage" phase, so be ready for some extra spunk!

Daily Routine & Essentials

Feeding Time

  • Twice a day: 63 grams per meal.
  • Pre-packaged for convenience!
  • 15-minute rule: Plate up if not finished.

Neon's Travel Bag

Favorite Toys Leash & Collar Chew Bones Eye/Ear Wipes Pin Brush

Grooming Needs

  • Brushing: Prevent mats in friction zones (armpits/ears).
  • Ear Care: Wipe weekly; monitor for redness or smell.

The Potty Protocol

When to go?

Immediately after waking, after meals, after play, and right before bed.

Success!

Lavish praise and a high-value treat immediately after they finish outside.

Accidents?

Never scold. Just clean thoroughly with enzymatic cleaner to remove the scent.

Pro Tips for Sitter

  • 1

    The Umbilical Tether: Keep him leashed to you when not crated to catch early "I gotta go" signals.

  • 2

    Crate is Safe: Use his crate for supervision breaks. Make it positive with a chew toy.

  • 3

    Mental Burnout: Scent work (hiding treats) is just as tiring as a walk for this smart guy!

Post-Surgery Care

Surgery: Neutered Feb 5, 2026.
Marker: Small green line tattoo near incision.
Check for: Redness, discharge, or large lumps at the site.

*Note: A small fluid pocket (seroma) can be normal post-surgery.

Local Safety (Lee's Summit)

Blue-Green Algae

Highly toxic! Found in ponds/lakes. Symptoms: Vomiting, drooling, seizures. Seek ER vet immediately if ingested.

Ticks & Mosquitoes

High local prevalence. Neon is on year-round prevention, but stay vigilant during walks.

"Hey Neon! What's the most important thing for us to remember this weekend?"

Neon says...

"Just keep me on my leash (it's the law!), give me plenty of sniff-walks, and don't forget my treats when I go potty outside! I'm bouncy and I might forget my manners, but I'm trying my best! Let's play!"
